I had used HTML,CSS AND JAVASCRIPT.
HTML defines the structure of your content, CSS determines the style and layout, and JavaScript makes the content interactive. 
Therefore, it makes the most sense to learn them in that order. 
JavaScript incorporates valuable skills such as object-oriented, functional, and imperative styles of programming.
CSS, or Cascading Style Sheets, works with HTML to create the format for web pages. It also helps adapt pages to different formats optimized for desktops or mobile devices.
JavaScript, often abbreviated to JS, is a front-end programming language. 
JS: It builds on top of both HTML and CSS. JavaScript takes the work done with HTML and CSS and turns it into something that a user can interact with
